{{Infobox scientist | name = Ernst Kötter | native_name = | native_name_lang = | image = <!--(filename only, i.e. without "File:" prefix)--> | imagesize = | alt = | caption = | birth_date = {{birth date|1859|8|7|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Berlin]] | death_date = {{death date and age|1922|1|26|1859|8|7|df=y}}<ref>[[German National Library]]: [http://d-nb.info/117530743/about Record] [http://d-nb.info/117530743/about/rdf Xml]</ref> | death_place = [[Aachen]] | death_cause = | resting_place = | resting_place_coordinates = <!--{{coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline,title}}--> | other_names = | residence = [[Berlin]], [[Aachen]] ([[Germany]]) | citizenship = | nationality = | fields = [[Mathematician]] | workplaces = | patrons = | alma_mater = [[Berlin University]] | thesis_title = Zur Theorie der Osculationen bei ebenen Curven 3. Ordnung | thesis_url = http://gdz-lucene.tc.sub.uni-goettingen.de/gcs/gcs?action=pdf&metsFile=PPN315205407&divID=LOG_0001&pagesize=original&pdfTitlePage=http://gdz.sub.uni-goettingen.de/dms/load/pdftitle/?metsFile=PPN315205407%7C&targetFileName=PPN315205407_LOG_0001.pdf& | thesis_year = 1884 | doctoral_advisor = | academic_advisors = [[Weierstraß]], [[Leopold Kronecker|Kronecker]] | doctoral_students = | notable_students = | known_for = | influences = | influenced = | awards = Price of the [[Berlin Royal Academy]], 1886 | author_abbrev_bot = | author_abbrev_zoo = | spouse = <!--(or | spouses = )--> | partner = <!--(or | partners = )--> | children = | signature = <!--(filename only)--> | signature_alt = | website = <!--{{URL|www.example.com}}--> | footnotes = }}
'''Ernst Kötter''' was a German mathematician who graduated in 1884 from Berlin University. His treatise ''"Fundamentals of a purely geometrical theory of [[algebraic plane curve]]s"'' gained the 1886 prize of the [[Berlin Royal Academy]].<ref>{{cite journal| author=Norman Fraser| title=Kötter's synthetic geometry of algebraic curves| journal=Proceedings of the Edinburgh Mathematical Society|date=Feb 1888| volume=7| pages=46–61| url=http://journals.cambridge.org/action/displayFulltext?type=1&fid=3146652&jid=PEM&volumeId=7&issueId=-1&aid=3131388&bodyId=&membershipNumber=&societyETOCSession=| doi=10.1017/s0013091500030364}} Here: p.46</ref> In 1901, he published his report on ''"The development of [[synthetic geometry]] from [[Monge]] to [[Karl Georg Christian von Staudt|Staudt]] (1847)"'';<ref>{{cite book| author=Ernst Kötter| title=Die Entwickelung der Synthetischen Geometrie von Monge bis auf Staudt (1847)| year=1901 |url=http://gdz-lucene.tc.sub.uni-goettingen.de/gcs/gcs?&action=pdf&metsFile=PPN37721857X_0005&divID=LOG_0035&pagesize=original&pdfTitlePage=http://gdz.sub.uni-goettingen.de/dms/load/pdftitle/?metsFile=PPN37721857X_0005%7C&targetFileName=PPN37721857X_0005_LOG_0035.pdf&}} (2012 Reprint as {{ISBN|1275932649}})</ref> it had been sent to the press as early as 1897, but completion was deferred by Kötter's appointment to [[Aachen University]] and a subsequent persisting illness.<ref>Kötter (1901), Preface, p.VIII</ref> He constructed a mobile wood model to illustrate the theorems of [[Dandelin spheres]].<ref>{{cite journal| journal=Jahresbericht der Deutschen Mathematiker-Vereinigung| volume=16 | year=1907 | title=Vermischtes (Miscellany) |page=82 |url=http://gdz.sub.uni-goettingen.de/dms/load/img/?PPN=PPN37721857X_0016&DMDID=DMDLOG_0016}}</ref><ref>[http://www.math.rug.nl/models/Serie32_nr2.html Illustration] of [[Groningen University]]</ref> <!---more notable facts yet to be gathered--->
In a discussion with [[Schoenflies]] and Kötter, [[Hilbert]] reportedly uttered his famous quotation according to which [[point (geometry)|point]]s, [[Line (geometry)|line]]s, and [[plane (geometry)|plane]]s in geometry could be named as well ''"tables, chairs, and beer mugs"''.<ref>{{cite book| author=[[Otto Blumenthal]]| title=Lebensgeschichte| year=1935| volume=3| pages=388–429| publisher=Julius Springer| editor=David Hilbert| series=Gesammelte Abhandlungen| url=http://gdz-lucene.tc.sub.uni-goettingen.de/gcs/gcs?action=pdf&metsFile=PPN237834022&divID=LOG_0001&pagesize=original&pdfTitlePage=http://gdz.sub.uni-goettingen.de/dms/load/pdftitle/?metsFile=PPN237834022%7C&targetFileName=PPN237834022_LOG_0001.pdf&}} Here: p.402-403</ref>
