The '''Italian Mathematical Union''' ({{lang-it|Unione Matematica Italiana}}) is a [[List of mathematical societies|mathematics society]] based in [[Italy]]. It was founded on December 7, 1922 by [[Luigi Bianchi]], [[Vito Volterra]], and most notably, [[Salvatore Pincherle]], who became the Union's first President. The Union's journal is the ''[[Bollettino dell'Unione Matematica Italiana]]'', which contains two sections: one for research papers, and one for expository articles.

The Italian mathematical union awards the [[Bartolozzi Prize]], the [[Caccioppoli Prize]] and the [[Stampacchia Medal]].

